        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3128139685" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7098709946461804574">I don&apos;t normally like cyberpunk and given the choice, I never would have picked this up. But a book club chose it, so I had to read it. And then I actually...liked it? I can&apos;t even put my finger on what exactly I liked about it. It was a romp through space without a storyline. The characters did not do anything meaningful or memorable. I just <i>enjoyed</i> myself.<br/><br/>It vaguely reminded me of the Culture series by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5807106.Iain_M__Banks' title='Iain M. Banks' rel='nofollow noopener'>Iain M. Banks</a>. If you are looking for something to fill the Banks shaped hole in your life, </span>
  <span id="freeText7098709946461804574" style="display:none">I don't normally like cyberpunk and given the choice, I never would have picked this up. But a book club chose it, so I had to read it. And then I actually...liked it? I can't even put my finger on what exactly I liked about it. It was a romp through space without a storyline. The characters did not do anything meaningful or memorable. I just <i>enjoyed</i> myself.<br /><br />It vaguely reminded me of the Culture series by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/5807106.Iain_M__Banks" title="Iain M. Banks" rel="nofollow noopener">Iain M. Banks</a>. If you are looking for something to fill the Banks shaped hole in your life, maybe this would be a good thing to pick up.</span>
